<p>The <code>sandbox</code> tag creates an isolated execution scope.</p>

<h2>Basic Sandbox</h2>
<pre>{open}set $value = 'original'{close}
{open}sandbox{close}
  {open}set $value = 'modified'{close}
  Inside: {open}$value{close}
{open}/sandbox{close}
Outside: {open}$value{close}</pre>
{set $value = 'original'}
{sandbox}
  {set $value = 'modified'}
  <p>Inside sandbox: {$value}</p>
{/sandbox}
<p>Outside sandbox: {$value} (unchanged)</p>

<h2>Sandbox vs Code</h2>
<table border="1" cellpadding="5">
  <tr><th>Feature</th><th>{open}code{close}</th><th>{open}sandbox{close}</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Variable isolation</td><td>No (shares scope)</td><td>Yes (isolated)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Changes propagate</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Use Case: Safe Execution</h2>
<pre>{open}sandbox{close}
  {open}!-- Code here cannot affect parent scope --{close}
  {open}set $temp = 'anything'{close}
{open}/sandbox{close}</pre>
{sandbox}
  {set $temp = 'temporary value'}
  <p>Temp inside: {$temp}</p>
{/sandbox}
<p>Temp outside: [{$temp}] (empty - not defined outside sandbox)</p>
